<!ENTITY SYSTEM_CONFIG_USERS_TOOL "User and Group Configuration Tool">
<!ENTITY SYSTEM_CONFIG_USERS_INVOCATION '
    <indexterm significance="normal"> 
        <primary><command>system-config-users</command> 
        </primary> 
        <see>&SYSTEM_CONFIG_USERS_TOOL;</see> 
    </indexterm> 

    <para>
        You must be running the <application>X</application> Window System and have root privileges to use the &SYSTEM_CONFIG_USERS_TOOL;. There are three ways to start the application:
    </para>
    <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>
                From the desktop, go to <menuchoice>&DISTRO_MAINMENU;<guisubmenu>System</guisubmenu><guisubmenu>Administration</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Users and Groups</guimenuitem></menuchoice>
            </para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
            <para>
                From the desktop, right-click on the fast user switch applet in the toolbar and select <guimenu>Edit Users and Groups</guimenu>.
            </para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
            <para>
                Type the command <command>system-config-users</command> at a shell prompt (for example, in an <application>XTerm</application> or a <application>GNOME</application> terminal).
            </para>
        </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
